        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40338",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mabe",
                        "name": "mabe",
                        "displayName": "Marc Bennewitz (private)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "??<script type=\"text\/javascript\" src=\"http:\/\/maps.google.com\/maps?file=api&v=2&sensor=false&key=XXX??\r\nThis is wrong because all special chars (', \", <, >, &, ...) have to be escaped within (x)html attributes and the headScript helper generates a complete html tag which would be wrong on non escaping.\r\n\r\nI don't see a bug here !",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mabe",
                        "name": "mabe",
                        "displayName": "Marc Bennewitz (private)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-02T06:22:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-02T06:22:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40339",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=panckreous",
                        "name": "panckreous",
                        "displayName": "Dan Berman",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "looks like Jira converted all the code. \r\n\r\nThe code is:\r\n$this->headScript()->appendFile(\"http:\/\/maps.google.com\/maps?file=api& ampv=2& ampsensor=false& ampkey=$gmapKey\");\r\n\r\n(spaces added in to avoid auto format)\r\n\r\npassing that in double escapes the ampersands to & amp; amp; (spaces added)\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=panckreous",
                        "name": "panckreous",
                        "displayName": "Dan Berman",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-02T06:54:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-02T06:54:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40345",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mabe",
                        "name": "mabe",
                        "displayName": "Marc Bennewitz (private)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The method doesn't expect pre-escaped arguments.\r\n-> The first argument must a valid url (or path), not html escaped.\r\n\r\nAdditionally you have to *urlencode* your key parameter.\r\n\r\nplease write:\r\n{code}\r\n$this->headScript()->appendFile('http:\/\/maps.google.com\/maps?file=api&v=2&sensor=false&key=' . urlencode($gmapKey));\r\n{code}\r\n\r\ninstead of:\r\n{code}\r\n$this->headScript()->appendFile(\"http:\/\/maps.google.com\/maps?file=api&  ampv=2& ampsensor=false& ampkey=$gmapKey\");\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mabe",
                        "name": "mabe",
                        "displayName": "Marc Bennewitz (private)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-02T12:51:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-02T12:51:00.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
